hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CI literally just typed: look at what I=E2=80=99m building and iden=
tify the top 5 companies in my area that would be good for a pilot for this=
=2E Then I go to LinkedIn and messag=
e them. If it=E2=80=99s not clear, I do t=
his in the source directory of the code of my app so the first thing it doe=
s is figure out what it is that I=E2=80=99m building.=E2=80=9D
3. Same as above, but instead, scraping GitHub repos, from Sergei Zotov [ h=
ttps://substack.com/redirect/c0361f56-2ce3-488c-93a6-9c8a29ebbd13?j=3DeyJ1I=
joiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CMy product masks sensitive data in code assistant queries. So Clau=
de Code proposed the idea to find potential leads in the GitHub repos, by s=
earching for the actual sensitive values in them (and whether in the repo w=
e see some evidence of using coding agents). This was actually genius=E2=80=
=94not only does it filter out a lot of companies, but it also provides ins=
tant value to the lead. Here=E2=80=99s what it came up with: repos list, pr=
iority score, even LinkedIn URL.=E2=80=9D
4. Noticing when you=E2=80=99re avoiding conflict, from Dan Shipper [ https=
://substack.com/redirect/1a1a346b-f02e-4331-ad72-c8d86f25bfb7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiN=
WtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CI download all of my meeting recordings, put them in a folder, and=
 ask Claude Code to tell me all of the times I=E2=80=99ve subtly avoided co=
nflict.=E2=80=9D
Pro tip: Use Granola [ https://substack.com/redirect/6fba74a6-1039-4ce0-833=
f-ec3dc0addf26?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAj=
MRMPOw0 ] (first year free [ https://substack.com/redirect/254cc1da-c08d-43=
c3-9d1a-5a85e0f5478c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6R=
xQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]!), and ask Claude Code how to download your meeting notes i=
nto a folder.
5. Figuring out why your computer is running slow, from Anthony Roux [ http=
s://substack.com/redirect/86638045-a71e-472a-b858-2112563ac210?j=3DeyJ1Ijoi=
NWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CI sometimes use Claude Code for system diagnostics when my Mac slo=
ws down.
I use it to check load averages, memory pressure, disk space, stuck process=
es, and swap activity, then it dives deeper to find what=E2=80=99s actually=
 causing issues. It can calculate cache sizes, check Docker usage, find Tim=
e Machine snapshots eating space, etc.
It is usually faster and more user-friendly than running all the commands a=
nd trying to extract the right numbers myself. It can explain what the anal=
yses mean and why they matter, and suggests fixes with the actual commands =
while assessing the risk of running each of them.=E2=80=9D
6. Cleaning up messy invoice files, from Martin Merschroth [ https://substa=
ck.com/redirect/5694d7ca-9ab9-4087-af5c-2f36d64b3784?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In=
0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CI use Claude Code to sort my invoices for taxes. It reads each fil=
e in a messy folder, renames it to =E2=80=98YYYY-MM-DD Vendor - Invoice - P=
roductOrService.pdf=E2=80=99, and moves it into the right folder.=E2=80=9D
7. Organizing files and folders across your computer, from Justin Dielmann =
[ https://substack.com/redirect/455046ca-6dc8-454d-91c5-98034f567104?j=3Dey=
J1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CFor me, staying organized is a huge chore. The cognitive load of f=
iguring out where to store files and keeping everything clean and up to dat=
e was insane. My hack: I run Claude Code from my home directory and use it =
as my personal organization assistant. I=E2=80=99ll ask it things like:
=E2=80=98Find duplicate files and help me decide which to keep=E2=80=99
=E2=80=98Organize these downloads into proper folders=E2=80=99
=E2=80=98Review my directory structure and suggest improvements=E2=80=99
=E2=80=98Find old files I probably don=E2=80=99t need anymore=E2=80=99
It=E2=80=99s like having a thoughtful assistant who actually understands co=
ntext and can make smart decisions about file organization. Game changer fo=
r reducing mental clutter.=E2=80=9D
