om/redirect/1216b754-f598-43e8-8391-490558691345?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zd=
zy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CI built my own DIY subagent last week to help me build a slide tow=
er for my son =F0=9F=98=80=E2=80=9D
The finished product:
9. Organizing scattered thoughts, from Helen Lee Kupp [ https://substack.co=
m/redirect/7fc0c217-9306-4bf1-94d2-92afdd3abf46?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdz=
y88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m a mom who voice-records ideas during morning stroller =
walks, not a developer. The terminal interface? Overwhelming at first. The =
word =E2=80=98Code=E2=80=99 . . . but what if I don=E2=80=99t have a =E2=80=
=98coding project=E2=80=99? After 3 weeks of struggling to organize my scat=
tered thoughts, I tried it anyway. And discovered something wild: Claude Co=
de isn=E2=80=99t about coding at all. It=E2=80=99s about having an AI that =
manages your entire process=E2=80=94whatever the goal might be.
How I use it:
=E2=86=92 Fed it rambling voice notes from stroller walks
=E2=86=92 It organized them into coherent research themes
=E2=86=92 Wrote a full article in my exact voice (pulled from my own exampl=
es!)
=E2=86=92 Created LinkedIn versions automatically (this post is one of them=
!)
=E2=86=92 Everything saved and ready to publish (including grabbing a scree=
nshot of the template repository that I=E2=80=99m adding here!)=E2=80=9D [H=
ere=E2=80=99s the repo [ https://substack.com/redirect/26e7955a-1a61-4f57-a=
5b3-f4f694f1dcdf?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4t=
AjMRMPOw0 ]]
9. Writing a job description, from Justin Bleuel [ https://substack.com/red=
irect/78c02cb0-bc67-494c-9b9e-953b011ed75c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YF=
xPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CI used it to generate a full job description, hiring plan, intervi=
ew plan, and rubric for a new role at Clay.
I made a folder with internal Notions of our hiring material for PMs, added=
 similar role JDs from other companies, then in planning mode asked to gene=
rate the same collateral for this new role.=E2=80=9D
11. Synthesizing transcripts of calls with customers, from Derek DeHart [ h=
ttps://substack.com/redirect/870ba889-e710-4b54-9893-62f6c861e65e?j=3DeyJ1I=
joiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CMy current Claude Code jam is synthesizing transcripts of calls wi=
th customers to compile evidence that supports or invalidates a running tal=
ly of assumptions/requirements/hypotheses/whatever. Given MCPs to interact =
with other tools in our productivity stack=E2=80=94Fireflies, Linear, Notio=
n, etc.=E2=80=94it=E2=80=99s become my hub for ongoing product research and=
 development.=E2=80=9D
12. Improving your writing, from Teresa Torres [ https://substack.com/redir=
ect/1948ca04-974d-4a1a-b72e-a567d5464e88?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxP=
mLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CI now write all of my content with Claude Code in VS Code. We iter=
ate on an outline, it helps me improve the hook, it conducts research for m=
e and adds citations to my outline, and it reviews and gives feedback on ea=
ch section as I write. It has completely changed the way I write.=E2=80=9D =
[Much more on Teresa=E2=80=99s process here [ https://substack.com/redirect=
/80742c7c-b79d-4efb-9bc8-0f344f844758?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQ=
Jf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]]
13. Working with audio files, from Dan Heller [ https://substack.com/redire=
ct/3283c8e6-233d-4849-99a5-77ef61bc6be4?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPm=
LQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m working with multiple audio files. I use Claude Code t=
o manipulate them, convert the sample rates, rename them, and translate the=
m from Portuguese to English.=E2=80=9D
14. Creating =E2=80=9Cself-driving=E2=80=9D documentation, from James Pembe=
r [ https://substack.com/redirect/0064719b-4d6d-4523-949d-d77e8652a382?j=3D=
eyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CThe most interesting use case we=E2=80=99re playing with is someth=
ing I call =E2=80=98self-driving documentation.=E2=80=99 Basically, how can=
 we give an Agent the responsibility of figuring out how/where our document=
ation can be better and more comprehensive. We=E2=80=99ve been experimentin=
g with using Claude Code together with Playwright [ https://substack.com/re=
direct/d3f9cb65-0c77-4b03-b651-2f53b350a850?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88Y=
FxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ] to automatically explore our softwar=
e independently, identify knowledge gaps in our documentation, and then cre=
ate those changes itself. Very promising!=E2=80=9D [More here [ https://sub=
stack.com/redirect/03352e24-83c7-4061-a97a-d105f8ac562d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN=
6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]]
15. Creating a self-improving feedback loop, from Gang Rui [ https://substa=
ck.com/redirect/495f23c6-62f8-4e47-a730-984c4cbe9060?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In=
0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CI created a slash command that analyzes my journal entries + Git c=
ommits (for the past 7 days; usually I use this weekly), spots gaps between=
 what I said vs. did, and suggests system improvements. Like having a COO t=
hat learns from my patterns.=E2=80=9D
16. Getting inspiration from competitors=E2=80=99 ads, from Sumant Subrahma=
nya [ https://substack.com/redirect/9ce2a1b2-273a-46a5-87d6-a78b85c92e84?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CExtract ads from competitors to find the problem, use case, or cop=
y/asset that=E2=80=99s working for them, and then repurpose it for my ads. =
Claude Code built out these scripts that would screen-grab all ads running =
on the ad library, and it=E2=80=99s super cool to watch it navigate to the =
browser and grab all screenshots in an almost =E2=80=98agentic=E2=80=99 way=
=2E=E2=80=9D
17. Automatically creating changelogs, from Manik Aggarwal [ https://substa=
ck.com/redirect/cd96ce7c-5688-4a7f-af8e-9d753d0d6c96?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In=
0.zdzy88YFxPmLQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CI use Claude Code to create user-facing changelogs. I ask Claude C=
ode to scan all commits from a specific time period, then pull in my change=
log guidelines. It drafts a clean, structured changelog that usually needs =
few quick edits. What earlier took me hours is now down to 10=E2=80=9315 mi=
nutes. Most of our changelog output is created with Claude Code, with a fin=
al polish done by me.=E2=80=9D
18. Building presentations, from Hank Yeomans [ https://substack.com/redire=
ct/41dbc8c3-5749-4397-99af-e8f055a7262d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiNWtiOTN6In0.zdzy88YFxPm=
LQJf9hshgUC7BDnPG6RxQ4tAjMRMPOw0 ]
=E2=80=9CAll my slide work is done in Claude Code as HTML, then imported in=
to PPT.
First, I make a couple of slides that I need with some simple but well-prom=
pted data, while also prompting to create them as html pages. Otherwise the=
y might get created as SVGs or =E2=80=98slop AI images.=E2=80=99 I work wit=
h Claude Code making any adjustments.
When I get it the way I want it, I ask Claude Code to make a template that =
I can use to ensure all future slides added are the same format, branding, =
look, and feel.=20
This template becomes an .md file (I=E2=80=99ve put a snippet of that file =
below). With html you can be extremely specific=E2=80=94=E2=80=98change thi=
s wording to say that=E2=80=99=E2=80=94and then you can use an MCP to view =
the =E2=80=98slides=E2=80=99 to show what you mean as well for greater cont=
ext. With this, I have added several more slides as well as changed others =
using the template to keep things the same. Yes, hallucinations happen, tha=
t has to be accepted going in. Someone who knows what they want and can art=
iculate what they want will not have too much trouble.
When I want to put these into PPT, I just do well-thought-out screenshots. =
But honestly, If I=E2=80=99m using these for a customer or some presentatio=
n, I just open a browser and I have =E2=80=98previous=E2=80=99 and =E2=80=
=98next=E2=80=99 buttons built into them so that I can click through. Claud=
e Code creates these as interactive html =E2=80=98slides=E2=80=99 so they r=
eact to the mouse.=E2=80=9D
